<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">27</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">5</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">Sep 1 2007</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">1495</span> - <span property="pageEnd">1509</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/17848705/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">17848705</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2007.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: Sep 1 2007</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.275075045">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keywords</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=ECG+%3D+electrocardiographic&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">ECG = electrocardiographic</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=MPR+%3D+multiplanar+reformation&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">MPR = multiplanar reformation</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=3D+%3D+three-dimensional&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">3D = three-dimensional</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">The factors affecting temporal and spatial resolution in cardiac imaging with multiple-row detector CT are discussed, along with reconstruction algorithms, reconstruction interval, pitch, radiation dose, and geometric efficiency.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-authors"><h4>Affiliations</h4><div id="con1" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Mahadevappa</span> <span property="familyName">Mahesh</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MS, PhD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Russell H. Morgan Department of Radiology and Radiological Science, Johns Hopkins University School of Medicine, 601 N Caroline St, Baltimore, MD 21287-0856 (M.M.); and the Department of Imaging Physics, University of Texas M. D. Anderson Cancer Center, Houston, Tex (D.D.C.). From the AAPM/RSNA Physics Tutorial at the 2005 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received March 12, 2007; revision requested April 4 and received May 21; accepted June 8. M.M. receives research support from Siemens; D.D.C. is a speaker for the Medical Technology Management Institute, Milwaukee, Wis.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Mahesh/Mahadevappa" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div><div id="con2" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Dianna D.</span> <span property="familyName">Cody</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">PhD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Russell H. Morgan Department of Radiology and Radiological Science, Johns Hopkins University School of Medicine, 601 N Caroline St, Baltimore, MD 21287-0856 (M.M.); and the Department of Imaging Physics, University of Texas M. D. Anderson Cancer Center, Houston, Tex (D.D.C.). From the AAPM/RSNA Physics Tutorial at the 2005 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received March 12, 2007; revision requested April 4 and received May 21; accepted June 8. M.M. receives research support from Siemens; D.D.C. is a speaker for the Medical Technology Management Institute, Milwaukee, Wis.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Cody/Dianna+D" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-authors-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="doc-footnote"><b>Address correspondence to</b> M.M. (e-mail: <i><a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#a0cdcdc1c8c5d3c8e0cac8cdc98ec5c4d5"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="620f0f030a07110a22080a0f0b4c070617">[email&#160;protected]</span></a></i>).</div></section></section></div><div id="core-collateral-metrics" data-active-pane="false"><header><h2><i class="icon-timeline" aria-hidden="true"></i>Metrics &amp; Citations</h2></header><section id="tab-metrics-inner" role="tabpanel"><h3>Metrics</h3><section>



        
